cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques for improving license plate recognition (LPR). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel end-to-end trainable network for image recovery, which involves optimization and multi-task fitting, indicating that it may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of denoising and rectification, which are related to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on two challenging LPR datasets, suggesting that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
